text: Etiandro Igualdin Tavares (born July 24, 1993) is a Bissau-Guinean footballer who last played as a forward for FC Tucson in USL League One.https://www.fctucson.com/news_article/show/1008346 ==Career== ===Professional=== On March 6, 2015, it was announced that Tavares signed a professional contract with USL club Real Monarchs SLC. On March 22, he made his professional debut in a 0–0 draw against LA Galaxy II. ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Bissau-Guinean footballers Category:Bissau-Guinean expatriate footballers Category:Arizona Western Matadors men's soccer players Category:Real Monarchs players Category:Fresno Fuego players Category:FC Tulsa players Category:Association football forwards Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States Category:USL Championship players Category:USL League Two players Category:FC Tucson players Category:USL League One players
